# format: nodes are bare objects; links carry "_link":true. graph-schema/2 human editing surface. Hand-placed real-world surfaces the Canvas OS plugs into / interacts with. origin:"manual", manual:true, by:"director". touches_internet drives per-node world routing (§4). band "world" (external surface) or "actor" (an agent/device acting on the OS). Each node links to the cv-primitive or layer hub it rides. MERGE: mn-browser asserts same_as the derived research node wm-d-native-host (Chrome Native Messaging Host) per §3.
{"id":"mn-email","label":"Email client (Gmail / Outlook)","origin":"manual","manual":true,"by":"director","band":"world","layer":"distribution","feature":"broker","bin":null,"touches_internet":true,"maturity":1.0,"summary":"Hosted mail surface (Gmail, Outlook/M365) the OS reads, drafts and files against via connectors; a primary inbound/outbound signal source.","why":"[ride] Survivability: feeds Bin2 brokerage — mail signals enter through the broker, not a side door. Failure-if-absent: no inbound work context; Microsoft Graph/Google own the mailbox. Leverage: ride the IMAP/Graph/Gmail API surface while keeping envelope-stamping and capability gates on-substrate."}
{"id":"mn-browser","label":"Web browser (Chrome / Safari)","origin":"manual","manual":true,"by":"director","band":"world","layer":"distribution","feature":"distribution","bin":null,"touches_internet":true,"same_as":["wm-d-native-host"],"maturity":1.0,"summary":"The browser surface Canvas reaches through an MV3 extension + native messaging host; render/input target and the bridge from web context into the broker.","why":"[ride] Survivability: the distribution reach surface (Bin0/Bin2 boundary). Failure-if-absent: no cross-surface install path; Apple/Google gate the browser. Leverage: ride the extension + native-messaging bridge so web signals route into the bus without bypassing it. (same_as wm-d-native-host — the research-derived native-messaging-host surface this manual node names.)"}
{"id":"mn-calendar","label":"Calendar (Google / Microsoft 365)","origin":"manual","manual":true,"by":"director","band":"world","layer":"distribution","feature":"broker","bin":null,"touches_internet":true,"maturity":1.0,"summary":"Hosted calendar (Google Calendar, M365) the OS reads and writes for scheduling and time-bound work-session context.","why":"[ride] Survivability: a time-context signal into Bin2/Bin1. Failure-if-absent: sessions lack temporal grounding; incumbents own the calendar graph. Leverage: ride CalDAV/Graph for read/write while session state lives on the governed tape."}
{"id":"mn-drive","label":"File system / Drive (Google Drive, OneDrive, local FS)","origin":"manual","manual":true,"by":"director","band":"world","layer":"ecosystem","feature":"memory","bin":null,"touches_internet":true,"maturity":1.0,"summary":"Cloud + local document stores the OS connects to for source artifacts; documents/drive connectors feed the append-only tape.","why":"[ride] Survivability: external memory feeding Bin1. Failure-if-absent: no source corpus; the cloud vendor holds the files. Leverage: ride Drive/OneDrive/FS connectors but persist governed copies + provenance on the tape, residency-scoped."}
{"id":"mn-messaging","label":"Slack / Teams messaging","origin":"manual","manual":true,"by":"director","band":"world","layer":"ecosystem","feature":"broker","bin":null,"touches_internet":true,"maturity":1.0,"summary":"Team-messaging surfaces (Slack, Microsoft Teams) the OS posts to and ingests from as a conversational signal channel.","why":"[ride] Survivability: a high-volume signal source into Bin2 brokerage. Failure-if-absent: no team-context channel; Teams/Slack own the conversation graph. Leverage: ride the Events/Webhook APIs through the broker so capability + compliance gates apply to every message touched."}
{"id":"mn-clipboard","label":"Native OS clipboard / accessibility APIs","origin":"manual","manual":true,"by":"director","band":"world","layer":"stack","feature":"capability","bin":null,"touches_internet":false,"maturity":1.0,"summary":"Host OS clipboard + accessibility (AX/UIA) APIs the OS uses to read screen context and inject input on-device; local-only, no network egress.","why":"[ride] Survivability: a local capability surface gated at Bin3. Failure-if-absent: no ambient on-screen context; the host OS gates AX permissions. Leverage: ride AX/clipboard under an explicit capability grant — internal-only, so it does NOT route to the world."}
{"id":"mn-idp","label":"Federated IdP (Passkeys / Entra / Google)","origin":"manual","manual":true,"by":"director","band":"world","layer":"identity","feature":"identity","bin":null,"touches_internet":true,"maturity":1.0,"summary":"External identity providers (Passkeys/WebAuthn, Microsoft Entra, Google) the OS federates against to anchor its trust root.","why":"[gate] Survivability: the upstream of Bin3 identity. Failure-if-absent: identity is captured by Apple/Microsoft and the ledger attribution is theirs not ours. Leverage: ride OIDC/WebAuthn for federation while the RS256/JWKS verification + tenant row-isolation stays on-substrate."}
{"id":"mn-cloud-api","label":"Cloud inference APIs (OpenAI / Anthropic / Gemini)","origin":"manual","manual":true,"by":"director","band":"world","layer":"cloud","feature":"ml","bin":null,"touches_internet":true,"maturity":1.0,"summary":"Frontier + cheap cloud inference endpoints the hybrid router calls for bulk and hard-reasoning tasks (deferred per #232 until the consumer $/token curve is measured).","why":"[ride] Survivability: the cloud tier of the deferred Bin-ML router. Failure-if-absent: no frontier reasoning path; Google/Apple win agentic UI. Leverage: ride metered cloud for bulk while keeping governance, residency and the cost model on-substrate."}
{"id":"mn-payment-rail","label":"Payment rails (Stripe / Interac / card networks)","origin":"manual","manual":true,"by":"director","band":"world","layer":"ecosystem","feature":"payments","bin":null,"touches_internet":true,"maturity":1.0,"summary":"External, licensed payment processors and rails the (structurally separated) Bin5 entity integrates — never embedded in the core OS.","why":"[separate] Survivability: the external surface of the deepest, highest-risk moat (Bin5). Failure-if-absent: no economic rail. Leverage: ride licensed rails (RPAA/AML-compliant) through a ring-fenced entity — embedding unregulated finance is the Ant annihilation path."}
{"id":"mn-user-device","label":"User device (Mac / iPhone / PC)","origin":"manual","manual":true,"by":"director","band":"actor","layer":"world","feature":"none","bin":null,"touches_internet":true,"maturity":1.0,"summary":"The end-user hardware the Canvas client runs on and the actor that originates intent into the broker; carries the hardware trust signal feeding identity.","why":"[ride] Survivability: the origin actor for every signal and a device-trust input to Bin3. Failure-if-absent: no client, no user, no hardware attestation. Leverage: ride device registration + hardware spec gate so device trust strengthens identity without owning the hardware."}
